<main>
	<!-- Hero Section -->
	<section class="py-16 md:py-24 bg-primary text-white">
		<div class="container mx-auto px-4">
			<div class="text-center max-w-4xl mx-auto">
				<h1 class="text-4xl md:text-5xl font-bold mb-6 font-heading">WHOLE-HOME HUMIDIFIER SOLUTIONS</h1>
				<p class="text-xl mb-8">Professional humidifier installation and service to maintain optimal humidity levels for
					improved comfort, health, and protection of your home in Belton, TX.</p>
			</div>
		</div>
	</section>

	<!-- Service Overview -->
	<section class="py-16 md:py-24 bg-white">
		<div class="container mx-auto px-4">
			<div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-12 items-center">
				<div>
					<div class="flex items-center mb-4">
						<div class="w-10 h-1 bg-accent mr-4"></div>
						<h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-primary font-heading">BALANCED HUMIDITY FOR BETTER LIVING</h2>
					</div>
					<h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-darkgray mb-6">
						COMBAT DRY AIR WITH WHOLE-HOME SOLUTIONS
					</h3>
					<p class="text-darkgray mb-4">
						During the heating season, indoor air can become extremely dry, causing a variety of problems for your home
						and health. At Alltek Services, we offer professional whole-home humidifier solutions that work with your
						HVAC system to maintain optimal humidity levels throughout your entire home.
					</p>
					<p class="text-darkgray mb-4">
						Unlike portable humidifiers that only affect a single room, whole-home humidifiers integrate with your
						existing heating and cooling system to add moisture to the air as it circulates through your ductwork. This
						provides consistent humidity levels in every room, creating a more comfortable and healthier indoor
						environment.
					</p>
					<p class="text-darkgray mb-8">
						Our certified technicians install and service a variety of whole-home humidifier types, including bypass
						humidifiers, fan-powered humidifiers, and steam humidifiers. We'll help you select the right system based on
						your home's size, your specific needs, and your budget, ensuring you get the most effective solution for
						maintaining proper indoor humidity levels.
					</p>
					<a
						href="/contact"
						class="inline-block bg-secondary hover:bg-secondary/90 text-white font-bold py-3 px-8 rounded-md transition-colors"
					>
						Schedule Consultation
					</a>
				</div>

				<div>
					<img
						src="/images/services/indoor-air-quality/air-quality-system.jpg"
						alt="HVAC technician installing a whole-home humidifier system in Belton, TX"
						class="rounded-lg shadow-xl w-full h-auto object-cover"
						width="608"
						height="416"
					/>
				</div>
			</div>
		</div>
	</section>

